content: Ludicorp created and maintained the Flickr website before it was acquired by Yahoo! in March 2005.

description: A GNE file is a webpage that is dynamically generated and used by the Flickr photo-sharing website. The pages are hosted on the server from where these are served to the requesting user’s browser. GNE files are similar to PHP and ASP pages, but are developed in a proprietary programming language whose details are not available for developer’s reference.

A GNE file is a dynamic webpage used by the Flickr photo-sharing website. GNE files are similar to .PHP and .ASP pages, but are written in a proprietary programming language. They were originally used by Game Never Ending, a computer game created by Ludicorp.
